posts.message:
It is mostly done as a matter of crossed wires. But I've added the feature where commits are posted as blog entries to the apps page. Not entirely intentional. But I was already down that rabbit hole so I kept going. I'll make the appropriate changes soon to move the git commit auto blogging over to the dev log page, which I've yet to make. ^^;

But it's progress! The site is starting to have some idea of the content that I want in it available. And I'm slowly starting to understand how to piece it all together. It is my first flask app after all. Man, never thought I'd be making web apps. I suppose I never really fancied myself as a mobile developer either. But here we are. Making kivy and flask apps.

TO THE KING!
